            "name": "Tzvi Porath",
            "bio": "Rabbi Tzvi Porath (1916-2007) was a Conservative Rabbi in the United States. After receiving smikhah, he serves as U.S. Army chaplain during World War II, and then went on to lead two Conservative shuls in suburban Washington. In 1952, he began serving Ohr Kodesh congregation in Chevy Chase. In 1984, he began serving Congregation Adat Reyim in Springfield, Virginia.",
